#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an10.33"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an10.33:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 10 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 10 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.33:0.2"
msgid "4. Upālivagga "
msgstr "4. With Upāli "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an10.33:0.3"
msgid "33. Ubbāhikāsutta "
msgstr "33. A Judge "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.72, sc1
msgctxt "an10.33:1.1"
msgid "“Katihi nu kho, bhante, dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu ubbāhikāya sammannitabbo”ti? "
msgstr "“Sir, how many qualities should a mendicant have to be agreed on as a judge?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.33:1.2"
msgid "“Dasahi kho, upāli, dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu ubbāhikāya sammannitabbo. "
msgstr "“Upāli, a mendicant should have ten qualities to be agreed on as a judge. "

msgctxt "an10.33:1.3"
msgid "Katamehi dasahi? "
msgstr "What ten? "

msgctxt "an10.33:1.4"
msgid "Idhupāli, bhikkhu sīlavā hoti; pātimokkhasaṃvarasaṃvuto viharati ācāragocarasampanno aṇumattesu vajjesu bhayadassāvī, samādāya sikkhati sikkhāpadesu; "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant is ethical, restrained in the monastic code, conducting themselves well and seeking alms in suitable places. Seeing danger in the slightest fault, they keep the rules they’ve undertaken. "

#. VAR: sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ → satthā sabyañjanā (bj)
msgctxt "an10.33:1.5"
msgid "bahussuto hoti sutadharo sutasannicayo, ye te dhammā ādikalyāṇā majjhekalyāṇā pariyosānakalyāṇā sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ abhivadanti, tathārūpāssa dhammā bahussutā honti dhātā vacasā paricitā manasānupekkhitā diṭṭhiyā suppaṭividdhā; "
msgstr "They’re very learned, remembering and keeping what they’ve learned. These teachings are good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, meaningful and well-phrased, describing a spiritual practice that’s entirely full and pure. They are very learned in such teachings, remembering them, reinforcing them by recitation, mentally scrutinizing them, and comprehending them theoretically. "

msgctxt "an10.33:1.6"
msgid "ubhayāni kho panassa pātimokkhāni vitthārena svāgatāni honti suvibhattāni suppavattīni suvinicchitāni suttaso anubyañjanaso; "
msgstr "Both monastic codes have been passed down to them in detail, well analyzed, well mastered, well judged in both the rules and accompanying material. "

msgctxt "an10.33:1.7"
msgid "vinaye kho pana ṭhito hoti asaṃhīro; "
msgstr "They’re firm and unfaltering in the training. "

msgctxt "an10.33:1.8"
msgid "paṭibalo hoti ubho atthapaccatthike saññāpetuṃ paññāpetuṃ nijjhāpetuṃ pekkhetuṃ pasādetuṃ; "
msgstr "When there are opposing parties, they’re able to persuade, advocate, and convince them, make them see the other side and trust each other. "

msgctxt "an10.33:1.9"
msgid "adhikaraṇasamuppādavūpasamakusalo hoti—"
msgstr "They’re skilled in raising and settling disciplinary issues. "

msgctxt "an10.33:1.10"
msgid "adhikaraṇaṃ jānāti; "
msgstr "They know what a disciplinary issue is. "

msgctxt "an10.33:1.11"
msgid "adhikaraṇasamudayaṃ jānāti; "
msgstr "They know how a disciplinary issue originates. "

msgctxt "an10.33:1.12"
msgid "adhikaraṇanirodhaṃ jānāti; "
msgstr "They know how a disciplinary issue ceases. "

msgctxt "an10.33:1.13"
msgid "adhikaraṇanirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ jānāti. "
msgstr "They know the practical way leading to the cessation of a disciplinary issue. "

msgctxt "an10.33:1.14"
msgid "Imehi kho, upāli, dasahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu ubbāhikāya sammannitabbo”ti. "
msgstr "A mendicant should have these ten qualities to be agreed on as a judge.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an10.33:1.15"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

